Year: The inventor of the Geiger counter
A page from our Sunday Morning yearbook: September 30, 1882, 136 years ago and BROWN... the day the future physicist Johann Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method for detecting and measuring radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the creation of the device known as the Geiger counter.
