Foreign buyers will be charged a higher stamp duty when buying property in the UK
Under new Conservative plans, foreign buyers will be charged a higher stamp duty on UK property purchases, with the extra money going to help the homeless.
This move will neutralize the success of Corbyn's efforts to attract young voters.
The increase in the stamp duty will affect those who do not pay taxes in the UK
The Treasury expects an increase of over 120 million pounds a year to help the homeless.
Theresa May will announce today the decision to increase the value of UK property tax on foreign buyers, with the additional proceeds going to help the homeless.
This move will be seen as an attempt to neutralize the success of Jeremy Corbyn's efforts to attract young voters by promising more affordable housing and targeting high-income people.
